<div id="pf21" class="pf w5 hb" data-page-no="21"><div class="pc pc21 w5 hb"><div class="t m2de x2e h16 y508 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 4 July 20-26 </div><div class="t m45e xc3 h23 y39d ff1 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MC2 52Ennufl </div><div class="t m45f xbb h27 y509 ff5 fs6 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">riEgin </div><div class="t m460 x87 h28 y509 ff3 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">[LIS </div><div class="t m461 x1e h29 y50a ff1 fs18 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">III </div><div class="t m362 x37 h16 y50b ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;For I know that my Redeemer lives, </div><div class="t m462 x53 h16 y446 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and at last he will stand upon the </div><div class="t mef x47 h16 y50c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">earth; </div><div class="t m463 x37 h16 y448 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and after my skin has been thus </div><div class="t m361 x47 h16 y9e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">destroyed, </div><div class="t m464 x53 h16 y50d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">then from my flesh I shall see </div><div class="t m465 x47 h16 y50e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God, </div><div class="t m466 x37 h16 y6e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">whom I shall see on my side, </div><div class="t m95 x53 h16 y44c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and my eyes shall behold, and not </div><div class="t m467 x55 h16 y44d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">another&quot; (Job 19:25-27, RSV). </div><div class="t m399 x37 h14 y44f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This lesson covers Job 12 through </div><div class="t m468 x0 h14 y450 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20. It seems proper to skip lightly over </div><div class="t m469 x1e h14 y50f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these chapters, because so much that </div><div class="t m27a x1e h14 y452 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">is said by the three friends is repetition </div><div class="t m46a x1e h14 y510 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of what th6y have already said in the </div><div class="t m3c5 x1e h14 y453 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">first dialogue. Someone has compared </div><div class="t m46b x1e h14 y511 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the speeches of Job&apos;s friends to a </div><div class="t m46c x1e h14 y512 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">series of wheels rotating on the same </div><div class="t m46d x1e h14 y39 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">axle. There is little progress, only </div><div class="t m46e x1e h14 y513 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">restatement of the erroneous </div><div class="t m46f x1e h14 y514 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">traditions of their time. </div><div class="t m470 x44 h14 y456 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s speeches are different. &quot;From </div><div class="t m261 x1e h14 y515 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the depths of discouragement and </div><div class="t m381 x1e h14 y458 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">despondency Job rose to the heights </div><div class="t m471 x1e h14 y459 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of implicit trust in the mercy and the </div><div class="t m472 x1e h14 y516 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">saving power of </div><div class="t m386 x25 h14 y45a ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God.&quot;—Prophets and </div><div class="t m393 x1e h14 y517 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Kings, </div><div class="t m3a6 x2 h14 y45b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 163. This spiritual progress </div><div class="t m2a5 x1e h14 y45c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was slow and painful, but it can be </div><div class="t m39e x4b h14 y45d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">seen in the successive speeches of </div><div class="t m473 x4b h14 y45e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job. This lesson will pick up some of </div><div class="t m474 x4b h14 y45f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">these evidences of dawn in the dark </div><div class="t m475 x4b h14 y518 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">night of Job&apos;s sorrow. </div><div class="t m476 x44 h14 y461 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It must be borne in mind that Job did </div><div class="t m477 x4b h14 y519 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">not have the slightest inkling of the </div><div class="t m478 x4b h14 y462 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reasons for his suffering. He knew </div><div class="t m479 x4b h14 y463 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nothing of the dialogue between the </div><div class="t m47a x4b h14 y88 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord and Satan. He did not know that </div><div class="t m47b x4b h14 y464 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">he was a test case before the universe </div><div class="t m47c x4b h14 y465 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as to whether anyone really served </div><div class="t m47d x21 h14 y51a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God out of pure loyalty and faith. </div><div class="t m47b x48 h14 y51b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It also must be remembered that Job </div><div class="t m47e x21 h14 y468 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must not be judged on the basis of his  </div><div class="t m47f x93 h14 y50b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">early discouragement or of his </div><div class="t m480 x93 h14 y51c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">repeated accusations against God. </div><div class="t m481 x93 h14 y51d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Lord evaluated Job during those </div><div class="t m482 x93 h14 y51e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">trying months of anguish, not on the </div><div class="t m483 x2f h14 y9e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">basis of his questions and complaints, </div><div class="t m484 x2f h14 y51f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but on the basis of what he would be </div><div class="t m485 x93 h14 y50e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">when he ultimately emerged from his </div><div class="t m486 x93 h14 y520 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dark night. God sees His people, not </div><div class="t m487 x93 h14 y521 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as they are, but as they will be. He is </div><div class="t m488 x2f h14 y522 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">like the parent who sees in the </div><div class="t m489 x2f h14 y255 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">immature child the eventual mature </div><div class="t m48a x2f h14 y523 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">man or woman—only God&apos;s </div><div class="t m328 x2f h14 ya6 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">foreknowledge is accurate and </div><div class="t m3a5 x2f h14 y524 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">complete. </div><div class="t m48b x27 h14 y525 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The </div><div class="t m37b xc h14 y526 ff6 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary </div><div class="t m48c x2f h14 y527 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">organizes the second dialogue, or </div><div class="t m48d x2f h14 y25a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cycle, as follows (see vol. 3, p. 496): </div><div class="t m48e x27 h14 y511 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m48f x9d h14 y528 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s first speech: he maintains </div><div class="t m490 x9d h14 y38 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his integrity, 12:1 to 14:22. </div><div class="t m491 x27 h14 yad ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m492 x71 h14 y529 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz&apos;s speech: he reproves </div><div class="t m493 x9d h14 yaf ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job for impiety, 15:1-35. </div><div class="t m494 x27 h14 yb1 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m10f x9d h14 yb2 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s second speech:, he accuses </div><div class="t m25d x9d h14 yb3 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his friends of being unmerciful, </div><div class="t m495 x71 h14 y515 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">16:1 to 17:16. </div><div class="t m496 x27 h14 y52a ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m497 x9d h14 y52b ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bildad&apos;s speech: he insists that </div><div class="t m3ac x9d h14 yb4 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">calamity overtakes the wicked, </div><div class="t m498 x71 h14 y516 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">18:1-21. </div><div class="t m44f x27 h14 y52c ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m499 x9d h14 y52d ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job&apos;s third speech: he expresses </div><div class="t m49a x9d h14 y52e ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">his belief in the resurrection, </div><div class="t m498 x71 h14 y52f ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19:1-29. </div><div class="t m46c x27 h14 y530 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m49b x9d h14 y530 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Zophar&apos;s speech: he describes </div><div class="t m49c x9d h14 y265 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the present and future </div><div class="t m49d x9d h14 y531 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">punishment of the wicked, </div><div class="t mf5 x9d h14 y532 ff5 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20:1-29. </div><div class="t m294 x2f h16 y533 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m63 x2f h16 yc0 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m2a0 x59 h16 y534 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Sovereignty of God </div><div class="t m36c xb0 h16 y535 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 12:12-14, 17-21) </div><div class="t m65 x2f h16 y464 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m387 x59 h16 y536 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Problem of Death </div><div class="t m151 xb0 h16 y537 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 14:10-13) </div><div class="t m67 x2f h16 y466 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t ma6 x59 h16 y538 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Trust in Tradition </div><div class="t m98 xb0 h16 y539 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 15:7-10) </div><div class="t m69 x2f h16 y53a ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m365 x59 h16 y329 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Words Versus Warmth </div><div class="t m298 xb0 h16 y53b ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:1-6) </div><div class="t m6b x2f h16 y53c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m1c7 x59 h16 y53c ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An Intercessor </div><div class="t m171 xb0 h16 yd0 ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 16:19; 19:25) </div><div class="t m6d x2f h16 y53d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m310 x59 h16 y53d ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Cry of Anguish </div><div class="t mc8 xb0 h16 y53e ff3 fsf fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 19:13-22) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
